{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0132w4SXWL2Ap9vYxcqXdi1R","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 30 — state corruption fix #14, no-op (2026-03-27T19:27Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **State corruption fix #14**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review`, phantom `1-1-foo` present, counts 75/70.\n     6→- Root cause fix IS in dist/index.js:2313 (`clean.startsWith(\"{\")` guard). The fix was built in session 29's commit.\n     7→- **Why corruption persists**: Ralph likely ran between session 29's commit and this session, using the OLD dist/ before session 29 rebuilt. The corruption is from a previous ralph iteration that ran before the fix was deployed.\n     8→- Fixed: restored all 4 stories to `done`, removed phantom, counts to 74/74.\n     9→- **This should be the LAST occurrence** — the fix is now in dist/ and committed.\n    10→- All 74 stories done. No actionable work. Sprint complete.\n    11→\n    12→## Token Report\n    13→- Total tool calls: ~15\n    14→- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 3, Glob: 2, Agent: 1, Bash: 1\n    15→- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads\n    16→- Redundant operations: Re-read of sprint-status.yaml due to concurrent modification\n    17→\n    18→### Session 29 — state corruption fix #13 + commit root cause fix (2026-03-27T19:22Z)\n    19→\n    20→- **State corruption fix #13**: Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json. Phantom `1-1-foo` re-appeared. sprint.total was 75, sprint.done was 70.\n    21→- **Root cause fix from session 22 was never committed** — the code changes to `ralph.ts` and `state.ts` existed only in the working tree. Ralph runs from committed/built code, so the fix was never active.\n    22→- Fixed: restored all 4 stories to `done`, removed phantom `1-1-foo`, fixed counts to 74/74.\n    23→- This session COMMITS the root cause fix so it persists across ralph iterations.\n    24→- All 152