the fix is deployed\n\nRead these files for context:\n1. _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md — session issues log with 14+ corruption incidents\n2. _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml — current sprint state\n3. Run `codeharness stats --save 2>&1` to generate cost report, then read _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md\n\nProduce a retrospective covering:\n1. Session summary — session 30 was another corruption fix, no-op\n2. Issues analysis — the 14 state corruption incidents today, root cause timeline, estimated waste\n3. Cost analysis from the cost report\n4. What went well — root cause eventually found and fixed (sessions 21-22), committed (29), built (30)\n5. What went wrong — 14 sessions wasted on the same bug, ~$25-30 estimated waste\n6. Lessons learned — build+commit fixes immediately, don't just edit source; ralph should have a state integrity check on startup\n7. Action items — verify corruption doesn't recur, consider adding a ralph startup guard that validates sprint-state.json\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md, append to it with a --- separator.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"ab8a1251edc2b1009","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Appended the session 30 retrospective to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n- **Sprint status:** 74/74 stories DONE, 17/17 epics complete\n- **Total project cost:** $670.44 across 4,953 API calls ($3.43 avg per story)\n- **State corruption waste:** ~$40-45 total (14 sessions + phantom `1-1-foo` at $15.70), roughly 6.5% of project budget\n- **Root cause fix gap:** 7 sessions between fix written (session 22) and fix deployed (session 29) because nobody committed/built\n- **Top cost driver:** Verification phase at 54.8% ($367.27), which is expected for this harness\n- **Biggest red flag in cost report:** `1-1-foo` phantom story in the top 10 most expensive stories at $15.70 — a non-existent story\n\nOpen action items: verify no recurrence, add ralph startup state integrity guard, implement circuit breaker for repeated fixes, clean up phantom cost data."}],"totalDurationMs":92664,"totalTokens":29713,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2694,"cache_read_input_tokens":26731,"output_tokens":287,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2694},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
